    <Folder>
      <name>Unidentified Males</name>
<Placemark>
        <name>1912 John Doe</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AE5a_GyLPyUX3LicsBUzgZ3v-nRazjIAOJdfAyisf_fj0aamfTE2H4MPQ1cLOz1LgH0H695U-vrCImLKtHys_lEUEEcEJ2SrBPJa7sekOR_2VtUtWPRXaXRpa2p6U20DUpmGhQzCw47be5b2XcPiqDH13oY_1FYqvCOy3IeOt-TtPOMPA0-54cfThjJqB68tPqzSyk9sJLDhsQKGl7lmWlPA3vVUdQve6AlZm8uEOI_WwXPLvp3vmAA74nWQ2BX3Qw?fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Found December 23, 1912, in an old shack near the Provo Pressed Brickyard (Van Gundy's Brickyard) in the area of 200 W 1400 N, Vineyard/Provo.<br>The man was estimated to be about 45 years old, about 6' tall, and weighed about 150 lbs.  The man had a sandy complexion, a "Roman nose" and a moustache. .<br>He was found wearing only a shirt, undershirt, and one sock. There was also an overcoat located near the makeshift bed. Police theorized others may have found his body prior to reporting and his other clothing and items of value were stolen.<br>The man was never identified and was buried on December 29, 1912 in the Provo City Cemetery.<br><br>No Case #, No Links<br>Please contact the Utah State Cold Case Tip Hotline: 833-DPS-SAFE (833-377-7233)<br><br><img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AE5a_GxdmaVw9kn6ZJNNX5g0Gw6ikOr4v2XUbs76LMXUxkUD_JT1gluRyevuWe_SvKSgfIRdafvdbFuFTo3Nvv71-SUgxF21Mle3H_USLOmdMrUOWIDAtZjcxtmuQeoCO6mar3aRFZMIxYnbnlEnLVz9azrR1zzHuNFddarfWDLmg36CvRNyMt4XQEK2NBsPCp-WqMJarU5IdyBgGg9lF7Ub7QHxBoxLKzqKYjrBYwpAuPxoWg6LRd-n6xAX1eDg2g?fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br><img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AE5a_Gw8K3ha691Shi44-Wx_oc31A6Dy70dZx_YOm7ghqB1DAKfcNOWHVkSoYvdEUwnykwU6t50YQwpOn_FE0VS3sf6hvEk3hmfkaaqKMM9cUbvZk8ysNGX5WI2ij9vKVoqGe2zkEdYkVyYey4NH09qWdomZIcgDgFAEYBmuenv6qrQ_j40Msqj8QA6gyGjRTCG080vjm01b55JhIWgB7ycfwlXCHYsvoS7LdMU-LtGnAjdLeKOMN0ohr8yuhlsSTQ?fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" />]]></description>
