    <Folder>
      <name>Missing Females</name>
<Placemark>
        <name>Frances Shurtleff Sessions, 1946</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AE5a_GymPRcoQssNGbvo16bWgmJL3cA2-eY6g0a2q_Sc9mFvHqTCyglnKuiQM7GZLTGeUkP59lsgPB6SPi8M3LWsCh6OxCOtq3ETANVSfbEiZPGHM-upHAvSbTMA6aml_8CxlzCBD_khpIJu6_Fuka9hmFmVAvd06joIq55Z52YwShafGpcGKG1o1sL3dAwv_MlIibLJQW_XGlNXXjA8LUjWLg1AlmPBkrTh8rR4IbVq15Mc8dGN4-6yreydBbPSkg?fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Last seen May 20, 1946, at her parents home at 916 26th St, Ogden. Her son had just been killed in a rock slide in Weber Canyon minutes before, and there were some sightings of her walking toward the canyon.<br><br>Ogden City Police Department Case #: 22G14442<br>https://bci.utah.gov/coldcases/frances-shurtleff-sessions/<br>DoeNetwork: https://www.doenetwork.org/cases/4511dfut.html<br>NamUs: https://www.namus.gov/MissingPersons/Case#/89538<br><br><img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AE5a_Gx1QW8oIDxzSfWvqs3qNVESJNBnG2cPvdDau1-18kEhp9Bxstag_AjKj57banJofufmWbQl0hedmrED3eWNbR17ot96Hxr2VmxQXs9xA-wgCTCrv8m_c-dLsJn6PBFx1IVf_i939nemrX7e7o-EzQL8R-QDqp7FrhVQDNl1r5-sGfUAXRVWo_heAjtqg9iwU6iZdQZgCi5ZC-DjmsSy77nHBA53atQ9BpbesrW8eWnm-mjBQpu35Jx8FHG22g?fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br><img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AE5a_GwZUsAtQBxIPfzXOK8TkKbUL_vas9ahQt6a0tmOmxSP20_Ll1etjGshiDcENZe58PON_gZ8cgy4x_lj2nf_YKEk91zJBaUTJs1617rSCT5X_06WTDvAMQTsKYu58lIGkMeWds5sASzJ8F2enJTihz7mZ1Qp2hGnTjeHOcbtmt6xr1YkZ4KMqW7shbPseRBf9kKXtyxHm5nwQIwLCV8L_3oCB64iraJpijrz3LTTj829-huN4hgz-DQjsXH9dQ?fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" />]]></description>
